    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8215</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Amsterdam</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mahin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 122</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1918</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department refers to your cablegram dated
                    April 20, 1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d137fn1">Not printed.</note> requesting
                    information as to whether the firms on the British statutory list are to be
                    considered as allies of the enemy in the event such firms do not fall within the
                    definition of the Trading with the Enemy Act, and informs you that this question
                    has been settled by the publication of the new unified list, in which list all
                    firms on the British statutory list which may properly appear upon the enemy
                    trading list of the United States have been published and those not within the
                    statute of the United States have been eliminated by the British from the
                    statutory list.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
